<!-- ==========================================================

Description:
Email action confirmation page.

This view is used to handle verification or password-related
actions triggered through an email link containing an
out-of-band (OOB) code.

Server Variables:
- oobCode → Secure action code injected from the backend.
  Used by client-side JavaScript to complete the verification
  or password reset process.

Responsibilities:
- Display confirmation message to the user.
- Expose the OOB code to frontend logic.
- Provide navigation back to login page.
- Support internationalization for dynamic text.

Structure:
- Includes global header and footer partials.
- Organized using BEM methodology.
- Divided into content message and navigation section.

Client-Side Behavior:
- The OOB code is stored in window.__OOB_CODE__.
- Frontend logic reads this value to:
  • Verify email address
  • Complete password reset
  • Confirm account-related actions
- Feedback handling is managed via JavaScript module.

Dependencies:
- linkconfirm.js
- firebase.js
- i18n system
- Global bundle.min.js

Security Notes:
- The OOB code is passed securely from the backend.
- No sensitive logic is executed directly in this template.
- All verification operations are handled client-side
  through Firebase or backend integration.

========================================================== -->

<%- include('partials/header') %>

<section class="confirm">
    <h1 class="confirm__title" data-i18n="confirmTitle"></h1>
    
    <div class="confirm__content">
        <p class="confirm__content--text" data-i18n="confirmText"></p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="confirm__links">
        <button href="/login" class="confirm__links--link" data-i18n="backToLogin"></button>
    </div>
</section>

<script>
  window.__OOB_CODE__ = "<%= oobCode %>";
  // The frontend script reads this code to complete
  // verification or password-related actions.
</script>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>